[normal]bs', and the choice of discs has 
[normal]dumbed
[normal] down dramatically. What a pity! 
[normal]The changes at Radio 3 are a national, and even an international, calamity. This once great 
[normal]programme
[normal] was the envy of musicians throughout the world. It has suffered more fundamental
[normal]ly than other stations. The excuse given: it needs to appeal to a larger audience. Why? The BBC now offers listeners several more Radio stations. Does anyone worry that the BBC Asian service is only listened to by a small proportion of the nation?  It is i
[normal]llogical to dumb down this quality station. Instead, why not nurture new listeners on other stations - Radio 2 and Radio 4 - (Recently, Radio 3 presented 3 weeks of film music, and yet one of the nation's finest composers, was allocated a week-end in this,
[normal] his centenary year!) The strategy has failed: fewer people listen to Radio 3 than ever before. This can only show that more former supporters are leaving than new listeners are joining. Does a second rate station attracting fewer listeners make sense?
[normal]Th
[normal]e latest listening figures show that the most 
[normal]dumbed
[normal] down 
[normal]programme
[normal] of all - the breakfast show on Radio 3 - lost 100,000 listeners in the last three month 
[normal]period :
[normal] loosing 16% of its listeners in 3 months is a disaster. The experiment has failed. 
[normal]The BB
[normal]C, and its excellent orchestras, 
[normal]champions
[normal] modern music at the Proms as it should. It must be the most generous commissioner of new musical works in the world but does it use its financial clout wisely?  The vast majority of these performances are the prem
[normal]iers and also the 
[normal]derniers
[normal]. Such a catalogue of total failures seems to be an extraordinary waste of public money.
[normal]BBC Radio 3 is paranoid about the success of Classic FM. Why? Both 
[normal]programmes
[normal] can be different and serve different members of society. 
[normal](Woul
[normal]d any one expect 'Simpson's-in-the-Strand' to add '
[normal]beefburgers
